acs.description: This module defines the Avocent MIB extensions to ACS60xx products.

acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Value.name: acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Value
acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Value.description: Current of the sensor 1 in this PDU unit in AMP. The value of this object is the actual current in AMP * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 5, the current is 0.5 AMP.)

acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Max.name: acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Max
acsPowerMgmtPDUTableCurrent1Max.description: Maximum current of the sensor 1 in this PDU unit in AMP. When the PDU does not have support for maximum value, the value will be 0. The value of this object is the actual current in AMP * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 5, the current is 0.5 AMP.) Clear this value, set it with Zero value.

acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperatureNOS.name: acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperatureNOS
acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperatureNOS.description: Number of temperature sensors in the PDU.

acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Value.name: acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Value
acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Value.description: Temperature of this PM unit in Celsius degrees. The value of this object is the actual temperature in degrees C * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 240, the temperature is 24 Celsius.) If the temperature measurement is not installed this value will be 0. Valid values are 5 to 999 ( 0.5 to 99.9 Celsius).

acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Max.name: acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Max
acsPowerMgmtPDUTableTemperature1Max.description: Maximum temperature detected in this PM unit in Celsius degrees. The value will be Zero when the PDU does not have support for maximum value. The value of this object is the actual temperature in degrees C * 10. You need to translate the readed value (Ex. : value is 240, the temperature is 24 Celsius.) If the temperature measurement is not installed this value will be 0. Valid values are 5 to 999 ( 0.5 to 99.9 Celsius). Set with Zero value to clear the max. temperature.

acsPowerMgmtOutletsTablePowerControl.description: A set value of power*(2-6) will send command to PDU. noAction(1) = always returned in a GET. Does nothing if SET. powerOn(2) = when SET the power On command is sent to PDU. powerOff(3) = when SET the power Off command is sent to PDU. powerCycle(4)=when SET the power cycle command is sent to PDU. powerLock(5)= when SET the power lock command is sent to PDU. powerUnlock(6)=when SET the power unlock command is sent to PDU. The powerLock and powerUnlock are valid only for Cyclades-PM PDUs
